cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.CR, cs.HC 

This paper analyzes the DBLP bibliographic database to study the role of single author publications in computer science literature, which is related to several sub-categories such as digital libraries (cs.DL), social and information networks (cs.SI), information retrieval (cs.IR), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The analysis of demographics and reception of single author publications can be related to the study of user behavior and preferences in digital libraries and social networks, while the analysis of citation statistics and PageRank scores can be related to information retrieval and ranking algorithms. The study of the scope and volume of single author publications can be related to cryptography and security, as well as human-computer interaction, where the length and complexity of papers can impact their usability and accessibility.
